node.title: Phoenix advance to knockout semi with nervous shootout victory over Melbourne City
node.description: The COVID-depleted City side still managed to hold Wellington scoreless through 120 minutes.
node.content: ["Midfielder Nicholas Pennington has slotted his spot-kick to send Wellington Phoenix into the FFA Cup knockout semi-finals with a nervous penaty shootout win over Melbourne City.", "In a quarter-final fixture postponed from last month, after City were riddled with positive COVID-19 tests, neither side were able to find the back of the net during 105 minutes of regulation and overtime, forcing a dreaded resolution from the penalty spot.", "More to come"]
